<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-07-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="45" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                    <head>No. 45.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Kasson</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-07-26"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 26, 1880</date>.
                            (Received August 12.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 343.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The harvest this year in Hungary, according to
                        the statistics gathered at Pesth, promises to be sufficient for home
                        consumption, and further to yield for export a quantity not less than
                        20,000,000 metric quintals.</p>
                    <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>JOHN A. KASSON.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>